ws/music/black-sabbath-interview-sharon-ozzy-osbourne-tony-iommi-health-birmingham-villa-park-final-show-new-material-3835523">speaking to <em>NME</em> alongside Tony Iommi at Villa Park</a> , Sharon explained that her husband was doing “really great” at the moment. She told us that Ozzy was feeling “very emotional” about the final Sabbath show, and that it was “what he wants”.</p><p> “He wants to say thank you to everybody. He didn&#39;t have that chance because of his illness, but now he does have the chance,” she added. “He&#39;s got Parkinson&#39;s, which we all know, but he&#39;s great and it doesn&#39;t affect his voice.”</p><p> Iommi then told <em>NME</em> that the Sabbath gig would “do him good”, explaining: “That&#39;s what it&#39;s all about: he wants to get out and do something.”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/zakk-wylde-recalls-most-wholesome-moment-on-tour-with-ozzy-osbourne-3851915">Zakk Wylde recalls most “wholesome” moment on tour with Ozzy Osbourne: “We were like a couple of naughty school kids”</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
